						<div class="postbody">There are PC graphics modes that are this way as well (planar).<br /><br />This is another thread that falls into the category of &quot;you aren't going to truly get an answer to your question because you're asking the wrong people&quot;.  You need to ask Nintendo Co. folks who designed the Famicom/NES this question.  Any other answer else is purely speculative -- period.<br /><br />My money is on an amalgamation of 1) existing methodology/technology/concepts that were out there (likely unpatented) that were already well-understood, and 2) cost.</div>

